_###_ Steps to Reproduce

1. CookieManager.Instance.RemoveAllCookie();
2.  CookieManager.Instance.hasCookies() is false;
3.  No cookies are removed from the browser 

Using MSAL.

`CookieManager.Instance.RemoveAllCookies(null);
            CookieManager.Instance.RemoveAllCookie();
            CookieManager.Instance.RemoveSessionCookie();
            CookieManager.Instance.Flush();`
### Expected Behavior
Cookies removed from browser and user has to revalidate credentials
### Actual Behavior
Credentials are cached and the user does not have to reenter the password.
